<headline>Freeze Warning issued April 20 at 6:10AM EDT until April 20 at 9:00AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...FREEZE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM EDT THIS MORNING...
* WHAT...Sub-freezing temperatures as low as 28 expected.
* WHERE...Portions of Virginia and North Carolina from the Blue
Ridge to the Piedmont, including Roanoke, Lynchburg, Danville,
Appomattox, Buckingham, Halifax, South Boston, Martinsville,
Mount Airy, Eden, Reidsville, Yadkinville and Yanceyville.
* WHEN...Until 9 AM EDT this morning.
* IMPACTS...Frost and freeze conditions will kill crops, other
sensitive vegetation and possibly damage unprotected outdoor
plumbing.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Temperatures will climb above freezing
after 9 AM. After that time, remove any coverings which were
placed over plants.</description>
<instruction>Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold. To prevent
freezing and possible bursting of outdoor water pipes they should
be drained, or allowed to drip slowly.</instruction>
